while this was good, i found the mint did not blend well with the rest of the salsa ingredients and my partner thought it was *different* (partner-speak for "it could have been better") The seafood was phenomenal --the tequila added a great flavour--wished i marinaded a little longer.

Rating: 4
LOVED this. After reading the other reviews, I decided to leave all of the ingredient amounts as is, even though I was halving the seafood amount. Also, I added ~1/4 cup finely chopped cilantro to the seafood marinade/sauce, which I think was a great addition. I didn't have tequila, so I used a little vodka and brandy. I marinaded the scallops and shrimp together, didn't seem to be a problem at all. After sauteing the seafood in the boiled marinade, and removing the seafood, I reduced the sauce a bit further, then poured it into the bowl of seafood, tossed, and served over buttery, garlicky rice pilaf. I chopped the salsa ingredients much finer than in the picture, and I think the texture was great this way. Everything was delicious!

Rating: 4
Have made this 3 times since looking up the recipe a few weeks ago - huge hit. Had no problems with marinating the seafood, and served it on a bed of delicately flavoured garlic/butter rice - was excellent, my daughter said it was "the best thing I've ever put in my mouth", (though she has said this about several dishes). Followed the recipe exactly, and whilst I loved the salsa combined with the seafood, it seemed to have a bitter aftertaste when tasted alone - not sure if this is the jalapeno or the fresh mint - will have to experiment, but wouldn't make the salsa to go with anything else unless I can eliminate the aftertaste. Mango and Avocado is a yummy combination, but I do have to be sure to pick an avocado which is a little firmer than I would usually pick otherwise it goes a little sloppy.

Rating: 4
Made this recipe for the first time last night exactly as suggested - salsa was delicious as was the seafood. My guests were impressed. Will definitely make this again!

