Rating: 3
Good and flavorful combo, especially the salsa, BUT one caution. I noticed after about 10 minutes of marinating the shrimp (didn't use scallops)they were starting to turn pink, so quick yanked them out of the marinade--this is how one makes ceviche! As it was, I thought the shrimp were a little tough, even with quick sauté. Salsa was tasty-- needs more mint.

Rating: 3
I agree with MCMoorman's review; the salsa was great but the seafood was good but nothing to write home about. I kept waiting for some depth of flavor, and I think MCMoorman's idea of griling the seafood would do it. The marinade boiled later to use as a sauce would be a nice compliment. The salsa is exceptional, again agreeing with MCMoorman to use a firm avocado; mine was too ripe. I did use the mint, I think that gave it a nice punch of flavor. Also served this over a long grain/wild rice mix, which I think is perfect for the dish. I'd make this again but would play with it a little more.

