Truly exceptional! I halved the amount of seafood for two people, but kept the rest of the ingredients as written - the sauce was fantastic and we ended up eating these burrito-style with a little sauce over the top. Outstanding, delicious, and healthy. I'm going to use the leftover salsa today on some grilled fish.

Rating: 4
Four fours for the Salsa. Use "firm- ripe" avocado and mango; Dice into small pieces. Added some Yellow Wax peppers, in addition to the jalapenos. Used cilantro - next time may try the mint. The seafood was good, but nothing to write home about. I did add mahi-mahi which worked well. Marinated the mahi- mahi; cooked on the grill; and then added to the saute with the scallops.

